# =============================================================================
# EMAIL CONFIGURATION (SMTP)
# =============================================================================
# ‚ö†Ô∏è ACTION REQUIRED: Configure before deployment!
# 
# IMPORTANT: To avoid spam rejection, use one of these options:
#
# Option 1: Gmail SMTP (Quick Start - May have deliverability issues)
#   PROS: Easy setup, free
#   CONS: 500 emails/day limit, may be rejected as spam by some providers
#   
#   Setup:
#   1. Enable 2FA: https://myaccount.google.com/security
#   2. Generate App Password: https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords
#   3. IMPORTANT: Use SAME email for SMTP_USER and EMAIL_FROM_ADDRESS
#      (Mismatched addresses trigger spam filters!)
#
#   Configuration:
SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
SMTP_PORT=587
SMTP_USER=your-email@gmail.com
SMTP_PASSWORD=your-gmail-app-password-16-chars
EMAIL_FROM_ADDRESS=your-email@gmail.com  # ‚ö†Ô∏è MUST match SMTP_USER to avoid spam!
EMAIL_FROM_NAME=Antystyki

#   To use custom domain (noreply@antystyki.pl):
#   - Add SPF record to DNS: v=spf1 include:_spf.google.com ~all
#   - Then you can use: EMAIL_FROM_ADDRESS=noreply@antystyki.pl
#   - See EMAIL_DELIVERABILITY_FIX.md for details
#
# Option 2: SendGrid (Recommended for production)
#   PROS: Best deliverability, 100 emails/day free, professional
#   CONS: Requires code changes, account setup
#   
#   Setup: See EMAIL_DELIVERABILITY_FIX.md Option 3
#   Configuration:
# SMTP_HOST=smtp.sendgrid.net
# SMTP_PORT=587
# SMTP_USER=apikey
# SMTP_PASSWORD=SG.your-sendgrid-api-key-here
# EMAIL_FROM_ADDRESS=noreply@antystyki.pl
# EMAIL_FROM_NAME=Antystyki

